<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
  <text>
    <body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1984-01-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1984-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                        <head>264. Telegram From the Embassy in the German Democratic Republic to
                            the Department of State.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d264fn1">Source: Reagan Library, Executive Secretariat, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Cable File, Europe (State) NODIS
                                IN (01/21/1984–04/23/1984). Confidential; Immediate;
                            Nodis.</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">278.</seg><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>East Berlin</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1984-01-27">January 27, 1984,
                            1240Z</date></dateline></opener>
                        <!--<pb facs="d264-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d264-2"/>-->
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item><rs corresp="reccPNaD9EAQIn4zj" type="topic">Asylum</rs> Seekers in Berlin.</item>
                        </list>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Confidential—Entire text.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>The <gloss target="#t_FRG_1">FRG</gloss>
                                <gloss target="#t_POLCOUNS_1">PolCouns</gloss> told us that as of
                                this morning January 27, there were asylum seekers present in the
                                    <gloss target="#t_UK_1">UK</gloss> and French Embassies and the
                                    <gloss target="#t_FRG_1">FRG</gloss> Permanent Mission in
                                Berlin. He would not add more except that the <gloss target="#t_FRG_1">FRG</gloss> Mission faced a difficult
                                situation which may involve three separate cases, all of whom
                                entered the <gloss target="#t_FRG_1">FRG</gloss> Mission this
                                morning.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RR_2"><hi rend="strong">Ridgway</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body>
  </text>
